#?IQR

My analysis of the GDP/employee data: I did some analysis on the GDP per employee data from the WorldBank. The data is from 128 countries over the period of 1980-2005. From the summary data, over the period of 1990-2005, the IQR steadily increased, but the maxiimum increased at a faster rate, and the minimum decreased every 5 year period except between 2000-2005. The data seems to show that more countries shifted into the IQR over time. If you view the frequency polygon plots in the links below, you will see that they all generate long-tailed graphs. If you view the last big spike in 1990 plot, you will see that spike shift in the positive direction after each 5 year period.
